06/01/2011
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Labour Minister Rasim Ljajic confirmed on Wednesday (January 5th) that any final decision regarding a government reshuffle will be made by the end of January. In an interview with RTS, he said the decision lies with leaders of the ruling coalition. No date for any meeting has been set yet, Ljajic added. Several politicians have hinted of a reshuffle recently, citing the need to reduce state administration and govern more efficiently. (RTS, Tanjug - 05/01/11)
